 which the correlation problem is based\non the frontier orbital $p$-$d$ antibonding bands is determined. It is found\nthat if an effective interaction $U$ is properly chosen the $d$-only model\nprovides a good account of the physics of the $d^1$ and $d^2$ materials.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Jul 2014 09:24:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Sep 2014 08:54:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-25"}
